      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of futility is a very rational response to the scale of the crisis you're seeing. When the foundation of the world feels unstable, trying to find \"small joys\" can indeed feel like denial. Instead of focusing on escaping the fire, maybe consider what kind of fire you want to be in—is it one that lets you feel the heat, or one that lets you find a space to simply be still? Acknowledging the weight of the end doesn't necessitate a complete surrender; it can be a point of profound, albeit painful, clarity.",
      "source": "target",
